devdoc.details: Bugs known: 1. A friend can vote more than once. While this was handy in testing our contract, it is undesirable as one could monopolise the selected venue.    Ideally, we should record a vote for a given address only once.    - added `friends[msg.sender].voted == false` in doVote function to ensure the voter has not voted before 2. The same restaurant and friend can be added multiple times leading to similar issues.    - enumerate existing restaurants and check if the restaurant already exists    - check if the friend's address already exists by checking if the name exists since doVote function checks if the friend's name exists before      allowing the friend to vote 3. While the contract is stuck at the doVote function, other functions can still be called. Also, once the voting starts, new venues and friends    can be added, making the whole process chaotic. In a typical voting process, voters are clear about who would vote and what to vote on before    voting starts to prevent any disputes. Hence, a good vote process should have well-defined create, vote open, and vote close phases.    - added state variable to keep track of the state of the contract (Creating, Voting, Ended, Cancelled)    - added modifiers to restrict functions to be called only in certain states 4. There is no way to disable the contract once it is deployed. Even the manager cannot do anything to stop the contract in case the team lunch    has to be cancelled.    - added cancelVoting function to allow the manager to cancel the contract 5. Gas consumption is not optimised. More simple data structures may help to reduce transaction fees.    - added unchecked for incrementing variable i in for loops    - remove initialisation of variable of 0    - added immutable type for manager variable since it will not be modified after contract construction    - rearrange the order of state variables, state variable and address variable are placed together to use one slot. Other comments: The contract below follows Natspec format: https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/v0.8.20/natspec-format.html along with the order of layout: https://docs.soliditylang.org/en/latest/style-guide.html#order-of-layout To show the bugs are fixed Contract Address: 0x02635535fD00449CcAB1d5961a2369B854Ae9A8A Bug 1: - Charlie tried to vote twice but it returns false for the second doVote function call.   https://sepolia.etherscan.io/tx/0xa67f15e27799e495d43ef740a678ebf52a8624498e0f2b02c1c33f938944a9bd Bug 2: - The same friend cannot be added multiple times.   https://sepolia.etherscan.io/tx/0x3712e476de603ed46801711e1365ac6acb3107df0535ab3a6b6a1b249b19b368 - The same restaurant cannot be added multiple times.   https://sepolia.etherscan.io/tx/0xe03c5a6c400fe60b1b423b4fa912ef8343435e306a9f399184d52f89bcf281b4 Bug 3: - Bob tried to vote in the creating state but failed.   https://sepolia.etherscan.io/tx/0x85be85a6a8c20e08e3248c11f236db433d10314b8ce15ea8a83426f1a35f005b - Bob tried to change the state of the contract from creating to voting but failed as he is not the manager.   https://sepolia.etherscan.io/tx/0x5ac030e060b6e29e822edc20e28c5ce16e79a19e91b0506f5113f14773360289 Bug 4 (using contract address 0xdCe03e7960870E43CC4EB603dfa3d4812DFAC0D4): - Bob tried to cancel the voting but fails because he is not the manager.   https://sepolia.etherscan.io/tx/0x837b77ba72423421955cdeab6bd564c8077f0a6fc02350982b9acf0aaca70d1a - Only Alice, the manager, can cancel the voting   https://sepolia.etherscan.io/tx/0xcdcbcbbbcd54b845c4c28a35d0a60b861a6d69f72eac7d3ee23b22a6ce37d73f

A friend can vote more than once. While this was handy in testing our contract, it is undesirable as one could monopolise the selected venue.    Ideally, we should record a vote for a given address only once.    - added `friends[msg.sender].voted == false` in doVote function to ensure the voter has not voted before 2. The same restaurant and friend can be added multiple times leading to similar issues.    - enumerate existing restaurants and check if the restaurant already exists    - check if the friend's address already exists by checking if the name exists since doVote function checks if the friend's name exists before      allowing the friend to vote 3. While the contract is stuck at the doVote function, other functions can still be called. Also, once the voting starts, new venues and friends    can be added, making the whole process chaotic. In a typical voting process, voters are clear about who would vote and what to vote on before    voting starts to prevent any disputes. Hence, a good vote process should have well-defined create, vote open, and vote close phases.    - added state variable to keep track of the state of the contract (Creating, Voting, Ended, Cancelled)    - added modifiers to restrict functions to be called only in certain states 4. There is no way to disable the contract once it is deployed. @title Contract to agree on the lunch venue
 @author Dilum Bandara , CSIRO’s Data61
 Edited by: Amos Tan, UNSW (z5440950) to fix bugs as mentioned in Lab 01
 @dev Bugs known:
 1. A friend can vote more than once. While this was handy in testing our contract, it is undesirable as one could monopolise the selected venue.
    Ideally, we should record a vote for a given address only once.
    - added `friends[msg.sender].voted == false` in doVote function to ensure the voter has not voted before
 2. The same restaurant and friend can be added multiple times leading to similar issues.
    - enumerate existing restaurants and check if the restaurant already exists
    - check if the friend's address already exists by checking if the name exists since doVote function checks if the friend's name exists before
      allowing the friend to vote
 3. While the contract is stuck at the doVote function, other functions can still be called. Also, once the voting starts, new venues and friends
    can be added, making the whole process chaotic. In a typical voting process, voters are clear about who would vote and what to vote on before
    voting starts to prevent any disputes. Hence, a good vote process should have well-defined create, vote open, and vote close phases.
    - added state variable to keep track of the state of the contract (Creating, Voting, Ended, Cancelled)
    - added modifiers to restrict functions to be called only in certain states
 4. There is no way to disable the contract once it is deployed. Even the manager cannot do anything to stop the contract in case the team lunch
    has to be cancelled.
    - added cancelVoting function to allow the manager to cancel the contract
 5. Gas consumption is not optimised. More simple data structures may help to reduce transaction fees.
    - added unchecked for incrementing variable i in for loops
    - remove initialisation of variable of 0
    - added immutable type for manager variable since it will not be modified after contract construction
    - rearrange the order of state variables, state variable and address variable are placed together to use one slot.
